//@version=5
indicator("LUKE WATCH FLAGSHIP - v4 Mancini Context Trusted", shorttitle="LUKE v4 CONTEXT", overlay=true, max_lines_count=260, max_labels_count=180)

// FLAGSHIP COPY - 2026-05-06
// Baseline: v4 trade math + friend ribbon compile fix.
// Current live TradingView read: 77% success, 10/13, about $1500 net.
// Same strategy as LUKE-WATCH-BEST-WORKING, with the two stats panels merged.
// The old event ledger table is intentionally removed; LONG boxes carry trade status.
// Signal timing can be confirmed_5m for audit/backtest or live_intrabar for execution.
// Live intrabar fizzles are marked CANCELLED immediately and counted separately, not as failed trades.
// Cancelled live LONGs also leave one active-watch marker for that same level.
// Restored trusted v4 with only Mancini + Saty level inputs active for live simplicity.
// Mancini context inputs are visual-only metadata and do not feed the signal engine.

// TradingView visual bridge only. This script does not submit orders, uses an
// indicator declaration only, and cannot read manual TradingView drawing objects.
// Realistic accounting keeps signal logic visual-only while letting costs model
// commission-only, one-way slippage, or both-side stress without changing fills.

enable_luke_levels = input.bool(true, "Enable Luke levels")
enable_saty = input.bool(true, "Enable Saty")
